FBIS4-37427 "drnes119_s_94013" FBIS-NES-94-119 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 Iran Bomb Explodes in Crowded Shrine in Mashhad Bomb Explodes in Crowded Shrine in Mashhad Shrine Reopens to Pilgrims LD2106103994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 21 Jun 94 LD2106103994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Excerpts] Latest reports received from Mashhad indicate that the holy shrine of Imam 'Ali Bin Musa al-Reza, peace be upon him, was opened this morning to the pilgrims eager to pay their respects. Our colleague has dispatched the following report: In the wake of the bloody tragedy of Mashhad and the massacre inside the holy shrine of Imam Reza, the shrine opened at 1130 today to the enthusiastic pilgrims. [passage omitted] Funeral ceremonies for the Ashura day martyrs in Mashhad will be staged in the city tomorrow morning.
